# FastAPI-Jet contribution standards

## Positioning

Modular FastAPI with a Django-inspired workflow. Optimize for day-2 structure, not full-stack codegen.

## Architecture rules

- Generated projects must **not** import `fastapi-jet` at runtime
- Routing bootstrap lives in `base/routing.py` (template) and `fastapi_jet/tools.py` (tests/back-compat) — **keep both in sync**
- Use `fastapi_jet.project` for cwd/sys.path/main-module loading in CLI commands
- Never capture `os.getcwd()` at import time; call `Path.cwd()` or `get_project_root()` at runtime

## Code quality

- Run `ruff check .` and `pytest` before opening a PR
- Prefer `importlib.import_module` over `__import__`
- Use `Path` for filesystem checks; use `str.translate` for bulk character replacement
- Trim verbose docstrings; code should be self-explanatory
- Minimize scope — no drive-by refactors or unrelated features

## CLI conventions

- Project-only commands use `@fastapi_project` and exit with code `1` on failure
- User-facing paths: `base/main.py`, `apps/<name>/routers.py`, `INSTALLED_APPS`
- Typer help text must match actual file/command names

## Tests

- Add tests for new commands and bug fixes
- Use `typer.testing.CliRunner` for CLI integration tests
- Template integration tests: set `HOME` to `tmp_path` for cookiecutter replay writes
- Mock external IO when unit-testing — cookiecutter integration uses real templates

## Generated project template

- New projects include: `pyproject.toml`, `.fastapi-jet`, sample `core` app, `/health`, pytest scaffold
- App templates: `app`, `app-crud`, `app-versioned`, `app-crud-versioned` — keep routing logic in sync with `fastapi_jet/tools.py`
- Validation logic lives in `fastapi_jet/checks.py`; `jet check` must stay in sync with template layout
- `INSTALLED_APPS` auto-registration lives in `fastapi_jet/register.py` (AST only, never regex)
- App conventions documented in `docs/CONVENTIONS.md`

## What not to add

- Full-stack generators (`jet add stripe`, DB wizards) unless strategy changes
- Runtime dependency on the CLI package inside generated projects
- Over-abstracted one-line helpers
